						               													<description>In Escargot Sprint, you play the role of a hungry little snail that spotted a lush garden at the other end of the terrace. But you are not alone, as several other snails will try to get get there first! Your goal is to reach the appetizing greenery before the competition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this push-your-luck game, the players will have access to four consecutive decks of cards, coloured green, yellow, orange and red respectively. Starting with the green deck, the player will draw cards, having the option to either stop afterwards or draw a card from the next deck of cards. Each consecutive deck contains more interesting cards that the last while also being more dangerous.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To move forward, the player must draw Raindrop cards in the decks, and will move forward from as many spaces as the number of raindrops they drew that turn. But the decks also contain Sun cards that will force the player to move their snail backwards and end their turn immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are also several item cards, such as the Salad, which prevent the player from moving backwards when drawing Sun cards, or the Umbrella, which prevents another player from moving during their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first snail to reach the garden wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
